title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 §§ 23-10.5 - Exhaust piping
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 §§ 23-10.5 - Exhaust piping

State Regulations

The exhaust piping of each internal combustion engine
shall be so installed as to discharge exhaust gases away from the operator and
any other pesrons working or passing nearby. Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12

23-10.5

State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
